Description: Thomson TO7-70 home computer emulator
 thom emulates the Thomson TO7-70, a French 8-bit home computer based on the
 Motorola MC6809E processor. It faithfully reproduces the hardware of the
 TO7-70, including the CPU, memory card, video card, and the following
 peripherals: optical pen (light pen), joysticks, cassette tape reader, and
 floppy disk controller.
 .
 The emulator runs in windowed mode under X11 (GTK+ 1.2) and supports the
 following virtual media formats:
  - Mémo7 ROM cartridge images (.m7)
  - Cassette tape images (.k7)
  - Thomson 5"25 floppy disk images (.sap)
 .
 Sound output is provided via PulseAudio. The control panel (ESC key) allows
 managing peripherals and adjusting the emulation speed.
